\par\b Inventory Control Program Status Summary\b0\par
Prepared on 2026-02-20 based on repository inspection, deployment documentation, and recent merge history.\par
This summary consolidates completed workstreams, current system readiness, outstanding technical blockers, and the specific decisions or inputs required from business owners to finish production rollout.\par
\par
\par\b 1) Executive Overview\b0\par
The project has progressed through a substantial multi-phase implementation cycle with at least twenty merged feature branches covering inventory CRUD, supplier management, transactions, barcode support, expiry tracking, recipes, waste tracking, count sessions, purchase-order automation, financial dashboards, multi-location capabilities, reporting/export flows, alerts, and production-hardening tasks.\par
At a feature level, the system appears functionally broad and near-complete for core operations. Documentation for deployment, operations, and staff usage is present. Administrative controls (status and cache invalidation) are documented and protected via token-based headers.\par
However, there is at least one active technical blocker discovered during validation: backend automated tests currently fail because of a JavaScript syntax error in the items route module. This indicates the codebase is not yet release-safe without a corrective patch and revalidation.\par
In parallel, production rollout cannot complete without user/owner inputs around infrastructure selection, secrets, policy settings, and operations ownership. These are listed explicitly in Section 6 so they can be actioned immediately.\par
