Documentation Maturity: Deployment and user manual docs are present and actionable. This significantly reduces onboarding risk for non-engineering operators.\par
\par
\par\b 4) Validation Findings from Current Check\b0\par
A direct backend test run was executed. The suite failed immediately due to a syntax error in backend/src/routes/items.js (unexpected token ')' near line 53), causing the Node test process to abort.\par
Impact: This is not a business-configuration issue; it is a code defect that blocks confidence in build stability. Even if deployment infrastructure is prepared, release should pause until this is patched and tests pass.\par
Risk Level: High for immediate production promotion, because test execution is currently non-green.\par
Recommended technical next action (engineering): Fix the syntax error, rerun backend tests, and perform smoke checks from the deployment runbook before any production cutover.\par
